CodeList.Name: Arm Null Reason

Description.TranslatedText: Terminology relevant to the reason for why an arm and/or an actual arm is null.

EnumeratedItem.nciodm:CDISCDefinition: The subject, who met eligibility criteria, was assigned to an arm but was not treated. (NCI)
EnumeratedItem.nciodm:PreferredTerm: Subject Assigned to Arm But Not Treated

EnumeratedItem.nciodm:CDISCDefinition: The subject, who met eligibility criteria, was not assigned to an arm and was not treated. (NCI)
The potential subject who does not meet one or more criteria required for participation in a trial.
The subject, who met eligibility criteria, was assigned to an arm but received treatment not associated with any of the planned arms.

CodeList.nciodm:PreferredTerm: CDISC SDTM Arm Null Reason Response Terminology
